title: Fatal crash in Sydney's northwest | 7NEWS
description: A fatal collision occurred in Sydney's northwest when a Mitsubishi Lancer struck the back of a tipper truck on Lane Cove Road at North Ryde after 1am. The male passenger died at the scene, whilst the driver and female passenger were trapped before being hospitalised in serious but stable condition. title: Hong Kong tower fire death toll rises to 146 | 7NEWS
description: A devastating apartment tower fire in Hong Kong has claimed 146 lives with 150 people still missing. Three people have been charged with manslaughter and eight others arrested on suspicion of corruption related to the fire that engulfed seven buildings. Mourners have formed queues stretching over a kilometre along a nearby canal to lay flowers in tribute to the victims. title: Pilot dies in midair collision at Sydney aerodrome | 7NEWS
description: A midair collision between two light aircraft during formation aerobatics at Wedderburn aerodrome in Sydney's southwest has killed experienced pilot Eddie Seve. The two Vans RV7 aircraft were part of a group of four performing formation flying when they collided as they prepared to land. While pilot Ollie Geraghty was able to land his damaged aircraft safely, Seve's plane crashed into nearby bushland, with his body found in the wreckage. title: NSW faces blackout warning over Eraring closure | 7NEWS
description: The Australian Energy Market Operator is warning that New South Wales faces potential blackouts from 2027 if the Eraring power station closes as scheduled. The report indicates that while renewable energy and transmission infrastructure are adequate, grid system security and synchronous condenser installation are not keeping pace with the transition. title: Queensland GPs now able to diagnose ADHD
